            {
                "s2_paper_id": "674cf24edc53f6fe242c1635002ae6983e9b1233",
                "title": "The Research on SOC Estimation of Lithium Battery Based on GWO-PF",
                "year": 2020,
                "venue": "2020 IEEE/IAS Industrial and Commercial Power System Asia (I&CPS Asia)",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 10,
                "abstract": "Accurate estimation of SOC of lithium battery is an important index for the safety and reliability of battery energy storage system. In this paper, a method of estimating SOC Based on GWO-PF is proposed. The particles are represented as gray wolf individuals, imitating the predatory process of gray wolf population, the particle approximates the posterior probability distribution and solves the problem of particle dilution in the traditional particle filter technology. Then, the state space model of the battery is constructed based on the second-order Thevenin battery equivalent model. The SOC simulation experiment of GWO-PF algorithm and standard PF algorithm is carried out under the condition of pulse discharge. Experimental results show that, compared with the traditional PF algorithm, GWO-PF based SOC estimation of lithium battery is more accurate, and has good adaptability and robustness to the process of nonlinear and non Gaussian SOC estimation of lithium battery.",
                "authors": [
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "2093520546",
                        "name": "Tian Dongdong"
                    },
